The paper deals with the estimation of mutual information, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Bayesian methods and prior distributions also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the discussion of numerical issues and the range of validity may indicate a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
